## This Document is a guide how to configure and validate the SNMP from EfficientIP ##

// ################## Procedure ############### // 

1. Admin Home Page > Authentication & Security > Network devices & SNMP profiles
2. Delete All SNMP PROFILES CONFIGURATION
3. Add New SNMP PROFILE CONFIGURATION 
    > On SNMP profile name > "Synetcom Profile"
    > Add Notes ( EfficientIP SNMP Profiles )
    > Choose SNMP version > v2c > Next                                             // In this guide ill choose snmp v2c
    > On Read community put the SNMP Community string > "SynetcomFM"               // You can define community string on your Own
    > then OK!
4. On Adminitration Tab go to Services and find SNMP Server
    > Click SNMP server > Next > Choose SNMP version v1/v2c > On Community put "SynetcomFM" > on SNMP restriction put "default"           // if you want to restric or hardened the SNMP you can specify which servers can read the SNMP protocol //
    > Click Add > Next > OK

To validate if the SNMP is working go to shell
from Client
% snmpwalk -v2c -c SynetcomFM -Of 192.168.71.101 1.3.6.1.4.1.2440.1.14              // snmpwalk 'version' -c 'Community string' 'Server IP Address' -Of 'print full OIDs on output'  'OIDs' //
*** If the Clients Received an Reply to Server the SNMP integration is Working Fine ***

from Server
% sudo tcpdump -i em1 port 161 and dst 192.168.71.110 | grep GetResponse            // This command it to validate the server got response to the client //


